article.headline: Lehigh 60, Dartmouth 50
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 29 points to lead Lehigh to a 60-50 win over Dartmouth on Saturday. Olivero shot 7-of-15 from the field and 12-of-15 from the free-throw line and was the only player scoring in double digits for Lehigh (2-2). Steve Callahan led Dartmouth (1-1) with 10 points and seven rebounds. Lehigh shot 47 percent, including 55 percent from beyond the 3-point line, in the first half and took a 38-25 lead into the break. Dartmouth cut a 15-point Lehigh lead to just 6 at one point in the second half, but the Mountain Hawks eventually pulled away. Joe Knight added nine points and six rebounds for Lehigh, while James Anderson chipped in seven points and four boards.
